{"author":{"id":"6da5b2dec6684e0fa0fdf37f95430cd11b5c1f44f89e673d57db05c9808aaf42"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1508142029,"nonce":"KCFHT2UcPp2ewVdIMUwSVzkenNo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjU2ODMxMzM=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1518","origin":"github"},"title":"Qiime summarize_taxa - Wrong revision on the MTS","message":"Hi everyone,\n\nAt the end of last week, I made an update pass of all the Qiime wrappers (from the IUC repository, MainToolShed) that we are using on a few Galaxy instances.\n\nI had no issue for most of them but after the update, the qiime_summarize_taxa repo was not displaying the little green icon indicating i was now using the last revision of this repository.\n\nSo I uninstalled and reinstalled this repo and finally got the green icon.\n\nHowever, when I edited a workflow that was using this tool, I noticed an error message about one of its parameters. And indeed, the parameter in question (`--upper_percentage`) was displayed in a red box with the following error message: `A real number or workflow parameter e.g. ${name} is required`\n\nI quickly saw that the issue was coming from a missing `optional=\"true\"` attribute but when i checked the last version of the code here on Github I noticed that the following commit from @bgruening was already fixing the issue: bd274e3 (2017-08-22)\n\nFrom what I understood, there should have been a new revision of the qiime_summarize_taxa repo created after this fix but it seems it wasn't the case on the MTS .\n\nI've just noticed this morning that the version date for both revision 5 and 6 of this repo on the MTS is **2017-08-05** while on the TTS revision 5 is from the **2017-08-04** and revision 6 from the **2017-08-22**.\n\nOn the TTS, revision 6 does include the fix for the `--upper_percentage` parameter but revision 6 on the MTS does not.\n\nDoes someone know why it's the case and how to fix it please ?\n\nThanks in advance\n\nping @shiltemann @bebatut","files":null}]}